    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      514.86,
      483.1,
      528.14
    ],
    "text": "In the case of Gooneratnayaka Vs. Clayton (1929) 31 NLR 132 Fisher CJ. held that;",
    "fonts": [
      "Times New Roman",
      "Times New Roman,BoldItalic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      108.02,
      549.54,
      526.27,
      562.82
    ],
    "text": "The writ of habeas corpus is not known to the Roman-Dutch law. It was extended to",
    "fonts": [
      "Times New Roman,Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      570.3,
      525.97,
      583.58
    ],
    "text": "Ceylon by the Charter of 1801 and 1833. The basis of the application is that the custody is",
    "fonts": [
      "Times New Roman,Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      590.94,
      526.42,
      604.22
    ],
    "text": "illegal. If a person, having the capacity to make a choice has done so, the Courts will not",
    "fonts": [
      "Times New Roman,Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      611.7,
      129.02,
      624.98
    ],
    "text": "interfere.",
    "fonts": [
      "Times New Roman,Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      646.38,
      526.37,
      659.66
    ],
    "text": "In the case of Rajeswari Chandrasekar Ganesh Vs. The State of Tamil Nadu - Writ Petition",
    "fonts": [
      "Times New Roman",
      "Times New Roman,BoldItalic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      667.05,
      335.71,
      680.33
    ],
    "text": "(Criminal) No. 402 of 2021 J.B.Pardiwala J. held that;",
    "fonts": [
      "Times New Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      108.02,
      701.73,
      526.05,
      715.01
    ],
    "text": "The exercise of the extraordinary jurisdiction for issuance of a writ of Habeas",
    "fonts": [
      "Times New Roman,Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      722.49,
      526.16,
      735.77
    ],
    "text": "Corpus would, therefore, be seen to be dependent on the jurisdictional fact where the",
    "fonts": [
      "Times New Roman,Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      743.12,
